        "cooked": "<p>This can be lumped under the general request thatâ€™s still open for all platforms:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"2568\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/_altj/48/908_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/scheduled-send-of-messages/2568\">Scheduled send of messages</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Be able to set a date/time for a message to be sent instead of sending it immediatlyâ€¦ \nThis is a common feature in most SMS apps.  My use case is for when I want to send a message to someone, but donâ€™t want it sent immediately. \nFor example, itâ€™s my friendâ€™s birthday tomorrow and I want to send him a message.  Instead of risking getting busy and forgetting to send it tomorrow (which happens a lot), I compose the message and schedule it to send automatically tomorrow at noon.\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
